Ùª­jAttributesÙ¯‚€öpExtended SummaryÙ¯‚‡Ù¹‚Ù§x¶Katz centrality computes the centrality for a node based on the centrality of its neighbors. It is a generalization of the eigenvector centrality. The Katz centrality for node $i$ is€Ù¤x.x_i = \alpha \sum_ { j} A_ { ij} x_j + \beta, Ù¹‚Ù§xHwhere $A$ is the adjacency matrix of graph G with eigenvalues $\lambda$.€Ù¹‚Ù§x9The parameter $\beta$ controls the initial centrality and€Ù¤x)\alpha < \frac { 1} { \lambda_ { \max}}. Ù¹‚Ù§y
Katz centrality computes the relative influence of a node within a network by measuring the number of the immediate neighbors (first degree nodes) and also all other nodes in the network that connect to the node under consideration through these immediate neighbors.€Ù¹‚Ù§ylExtra weight can be provided to immediate neighbors through the parameter $\beta$.  Connections made with distant neighbors are, however, penalized by an attenuation factor $\alpha$ which should be strictly less than the inverse largest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix in order for the Katz centrality to be computed correctly. More information is provided in .€ögMethodsÙ¯‚€öeNotesÙ¯‚„Ù¹‚Ù§x#Katz centrality was introduced by .€Ù¹‚‹Ù§xƒThis algorithm it uses the power method to find the eigenvector corresponding to the largest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix of Ù¡aGÙ§p. The parameter Ù¡ealphaÙ§xƒ should be strictly less than the inverse of largest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix for the algorithm to converge. You can use Ù¡xmax(nx.adjacency_spectrum(G))Ù§xg to get $\lambda_{\max}$ the largest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix. The iteration will stop after Ù¡hmax_iterÙ§x% iterations or an error tolerance of Ù¡xnumber_of_nodes(G) * tolÙ§r has been reached.€Ù¹‚Ù§xfWhen $\alpha = 1/\lambda_{\max}$ and $\beta=0$, Katz centrality is the same as eigenvector centrality.€Ù¹‚ƒÙ§xFor directed graphs this finds "left" eigenvectors which corresponds to the in-edges in the graph. For out-edges Katz centrality first reverse the graph with Ù¡kG.reverse()Ù§a.€öpOther ParametersÙ¯‚€öjParametersÙ¯‚ˆÙ°ƒaGegraphÙ¹‚Ù§qA NetworkX graph.€Ù°ƒealphaefloatÙ¹‚Ù§rAttenuation factor€Ù°ƒdbetax,scalar or dictionary, optional (default=1.0)Ù¹‚Ù§xsWeight attributed to the immediate neighborhood. If not a scalar, the dictionary must have an value for every node.€Ù°ƒhmax_iterx integer, optional (default=1000)Ù¹‚Ù§x-Maximum number of iterations in power method.€Ù°ƒctolx float, optional